00:00:28.470 --> 00:00:34.230
JULIAN BEINART:
Anyway, I'd better

00:00:34.230 --> 00:00:38.700
abbreviate all this stuff
that I want to cover today.

00:00:38.700 --> 00:00:43.410
The next three classes
are going to cover

00:00:43.410 --> 00:00:55.500
cases of very complex,
but very direct,

00:00:55.500 --> 00:01:02.100
relationships between social
and spatial structure.

00:01:02.100 --> 00:01:09.420
There is a literature
largely from the left side

00:01:09.420 --> 00:01:13.680
of the market on these issues.

00:01:13.680 --> 00:01:18.190
I don't have time to go
through much of this here.

00:01:20.970 --> 00:01:23.430
You should read the
required reading

00:01:23.430 --> 00:01:26.130
for this class,
Kevin Lynch's piece--

00:01:26.130 --> 00:01:30.540
chapter on social and spatial
structure relationships.

00:01:34.190 --> 00:01:48.430
On the left, I would
assume the argument--

00:01:48.430 --> 00:01:55.630
that space is an active agent,
that it involves conflict,

00:01:55.630 --> 00:01:57.910
that it's political--

00:01:57.910 --> 00:02:02.020
and this is an argument that
is articulated very well

00:02:02.020 --> 00:02:05.980
by Henri Lefebvre in the
translation of his writing

00:02:05.980 --> 00:02:08.229
into English.

00:02:08.229 --> 00:02:12.460
David Harvey's first book,
Social Justice In The City,

00:02:12.460 --> 00:02:19.180
argues that, under capitalism,
investment will never

00:02:19.180 --> 00:02:24.040
stream towards the poorer
sections of the society,

00:02:24.040 --> 00:02:29.920
because capitalism has so
many circuits of investment.

00:02:29.920 --> 00:02:32.260
An object of
capitalist investment

00:02:32.260 --> 00:02:35.680
is always maximizing profit.

00:02:35.680 --> 00:02:41.020
There are less
attractive writings

00:02:41.020 --> 00:02:51.330
by Manuel Castells in his
pre-Berkeley stage, the book,

00:02:51.330 --> 00:02:57.390
The Urban Question,
and so on, and so on.

00:02:57.390 --> 00:03:03.480
There's David Gordon's
writing about the origins

00:03:03.480 --> 00:03:07.980
of American suburbia as
being the result of labor

00:03:07.980 --> 00:03:10.470
friction in the
central business area,

00:03:10.470 --> 00:03:14.850
and the bosses wanting to move
as far away from the workers as

00:03:14.850 --> 00:03:16.140
possible.

00:03:16.140 --> 00:03:18.990
And there are many
histories of this kind.

00:03:18.990 --> 00:03:22.170
Castells' piece,
The Wild City, which

00:03:22.170 --> 00:03:27.090
argues that suburbia is a
form of advanced capitalist

00:03:27.090 --> 00:03:34.690
investment in which you
have to create markets

00:03:34.690 --> 00:03:41.200
for prolific domestic
goods, and suburbia

00:03:41.200 --> 00:03:44.680
is an attractive avenue
for this kind of market.

00:03:44.680 --> 00:03:47.025
His writing is
called The Wild City.

00:03:47.025 --> 00:03:50.920
He claims the American
city wild in the sense

00:03:50.920 --> 00:03:58.630
that it obeys the
consequences of market action

00:03:58.630 --> 00:04:04.430
in a very obvious kind of way.

00:04:04.430 --> 00:04:09.250
It's not hidden or transformed.

00:04:09.250 --> 00:04:12.010
There's an enormous
amount of writing.

00:04:12.010 --> 00:04:18.550
There's this writing and from
the center and the right.

00:04:18.550 --> 00:04:21.190
In Sunday's New
York Times, there's

00:04:21.190 --> 00:04:27.340
a piece called "Suburban
Disequilibrium."

00:04:27.340 --> 00:04:31.945
I don't know if anybody
looks at these things.

00:04:31.945 --> 00:04:37.800
It simply says that suburbs
are an equal, something

00:04:37.800 --> 00:04:42.890
that one would presume to know.

00:04:42.890 --> 00:04:46.400
And the reason suburbs
are unequal are given,

00:04:46.400 --> 00:04:48.650
and they haven't changed--

00:04:48.650 --> 00:04:50.900
and not much has changed.

00:04:50.900 --> 00:04:55.460
She cites examples of
suburbs close together

00:04:55.460 --> 00:05:00.986
in Los Angeles, where one
house sells for $68 million.

00:05:00.986 --> 00:05:03.605
And a few miles away,
there's a suburb

00:05:03.605 --> 00:05:07.580
of Mexican-American
workers who can barely

00:05:07.580 --> 00:05:08.915
afford to buy their house.

00:05:12.650 --> 00:05:17.390
In teaching this material,
I found over the years

00:05:17.390 --> 00:05:29.240
that the material is very
much stretched to large ideas

00:05:29.240 --> 00:05:34.100
about economic science
and social policy.

00:05:34.100 --> 00:05:39.440
There's very little discussion
of the meaning of place.

00:05:39.440 --> 00:05:45.650
Donald Appleyard has written
about that and some others--

00:05:45.650 --> 00:05:51.330
what place means, what space
means to people, and so on.

00:05:51.330 --> 00:05:55.040
So I've decided to
follow a different route

00:05:55.040 --> 00:05:59.000
in dealing with this.

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:07.280
I've established a notion
called "bipolarity"

00:06:07.280 --> 00:06:16.220
and chosen cases where the
conflict between various groups

00:06:16.220 --> 00:06:27.090
in the city is very explicit
and under different conditions.

00:06:27.090 --> 00:06:36.390
So we will examine Johannesburg
from its origins in 1876,

00:06:36.390 --> 00:06:45.210
I think, to today, following a
path of explicit racial policy.

00:06:45.210 --> 00:06:52.070
South Africa invented or
formalized racial policy

00:06:52.070 --> 00:06:55.700
to an extent that no other
country and no other state

00:06:55.700 --> 00:06:57.950
in the world ever has.

00:06:57.950 --> 00:06:59.960
So we should look at
Johannesburg and what

00:06:59.960 --> 00:07:03.320
this space of Johannesburg
looks like as a result

00:07:03.320 --> 00:07:07.760
of the enforcement of absolute
inequities between White

00:07:07.760 --> 00:07:10.040
and Black.

00:07:10.040 --> 00:07:13.390
We should look at
the colonial city.

00:07:13.390 --> 00:07:16.760
We look at Delhi and New Delhi.

00:07:16.760 --> 00:07:22.430
We look at the border between
Mexico and the United States

00:07:22.430 --> 00:07:30.890
and look at the polarity
between country and city

00:07:30.890 --> 00:07:32.765
in the development of Havana.

00:07:37.160 --> 00:07:42.020
Today's class is really
dealing with the mother

00:07:42.020 --> 00:07:47.120
of all social complexities,
and that's Jerusalem.

00:07:47.120 --> 00:07:49.310
I want to do a case
study on Jerusalem.

00:07:49.310 --> 00:07:54.020
And just for those of you
who haven't read the required

00:07:54.020 --> 00:07:56.220
reading for today--

00:07:56.220 --> 00:08:00.290
which is a long piece which
I wrote after months of work,

00:08:00.290 --> 00:08:02.810
and I'm so sad that
you haven't read it--

00:08:08.530 --> 00:08:11.470
I'll go through the very--

00:08:11.470 --> 00:08:15.520
let me just explain what
I've handed out to you.

00:08:15.520 --> 00:08:18.460
After this, the
map of the history

00:08:18.460 --> 00:08:23.200
of Jerusalem, a simplified
history, on the next page

00:08:23.200 --> 00:08:23.785
is a drawing.

00:08:26.500 --> 00:08:31.620
It's a drawing on a napkin
by the head of the planning

00:08:31.620 --> 00:08:36.330
section of MOPIC, the
Palestinian organization

00:08:36.330 --> 00:08:41.280
after the Oslo Accords, which
I worked with for a while.

00:08:41.280 --> 00:08:44.880
This was the depiction of
the future of Jerusalem--

00:08:44.880 --> 00:08:51.210
as one metropolitan area with
the Jewish sect on the West,

00:08:51.210 --> 00:08:55.050
and the Palestinian
sect on the right,

00:08:55.050 --> 00:08:58.380
and the historic
center in the middle.

00:08:58.380 --> 00:09:07.250
Below that is a letter,
which is obvious,

00:09:07.250 --> 00:09:11.810
pointing out the
stupidity of some

00:09:11.810 --> 00:09:14.370
of the writing on this issue.

00:09:14.370 --> 00:09:19.160
So what I'm going to
do is try to take you

00:09:19.160 --> 00:09:24.560
through a history,
which starts off

00:09:24.560 --> 00:09:28.010
as a history, for a
long time, a history

00:09:28.010 --> 00:09:35.990
of religious consequence,
and transforms much later

00:09:35.990 --> 00:09:40.040
and in recent times,
certainly in this century,

00:09:40.040 --> 00:09:44.540
into a geopolitical conflict.

00:09:44.540 --> 00:09:47.255
And we end up with
the status quo.

00:09:51.680 --> 00:09:56.720
Let's follow this
map very briefly.

00:10:00.240 --> 00:10:05.700
The origins of Jerusalem
are, again, political.

00:10:05.700 --> 00:10:11.280
For Palestinians, it
talks about the Jebusites,

00:10:11.280 --> 00:10:16.440
and the Canaanites, and
the origins of the city

00:10:16.440 --> 00:10:22.800
prior to 1,000 BC,
which is the date

00:10:22.800 --> 00:10:30.690
that the Davidian City, the City
of David, argues its beginning.

00:10:35.340 --> 00:10:38.150
David captures Jerusalem,
according to this.

00:10:38.150 --> 00:10:42.760
This is an Israeli map.

00:10:42.760 --> 00:10:48.190
According to the
Israeli history,

00:10:48.190 --> 00:10:52.750
David bought the threshing
fields on the Temple Mount

00:10:52.750 --> 00:10:57.610
from the Jebusites for 15
shekels, the equivalent

00:10:57.610 --> 00:11:00.310
amount of money.

00:11:00.310 --> 00:11:08.560
And in order to unify the
spread out of Jewish tribes,

00:11:08.560 --> 00:11:10.970
he built the first--

00:11:10.970 --> 00:11:16.660
he was a lover, and a
poet, and a general,

00:11:16.660 --> 00:11:20.170
and according to
strict Hebrew law,

00:11:20.170 --> 00:11:23.690
was not able to build a temple.

00:11:23.690 --> 00:11:29.110
So his son, Solomon, was the
author of the first temple.

00:11:29.110 --> 00:11:32.780
I'll show you a
drawing, by Corbusier

00:11:32.780 --> 00:11:44.050
of the tribal environment,
which the Jews, and most people,

00:11:44.050 --> 00:11:46.750
established at the time.

00:11:46.750 --> 00:11:54.550
And the drawing shows the temple
as the first physical presence

00:11:54.550 --> 00:11:55.195
in a city.

00:11:58.140 --> 00:12:00.960
Seeing that the religious
city for a long time

00:12:00.960 --> 00:12:04.680
just depended on a
religious infrastructure,

00:12:04.680 --> 00:12:06.795
it's clear that
the first temple--

00:12:10.870 --> 00:12:21.910
this temple exists for about
500 years, during which time

00:12:21.910 --> 00:12:27.920
the Middle East undergoes
sieges and invasions.

00:12:27.920 --> 00:12:32.650
The most significant
invasion is by Nebuchadnezzar

00:12:32.650 --> 00:12:35.860
in the 6th Century.

00:12:35.860 --> 00:12:39.490
This has enormous
consequences historically,

00:12:39.490 --> 00:12:44.380
and I tend to
exaggerate some of them.

00:12:44.380 --> 00:12:49.270
Nebuchadnezzar came from
the world's greatest city

00:12:49.270 --> 00:12:56.320
at the time, Babylon, the
most advanced city of all.

00:12:56.320 --> 00:13:00.250
Instead of killing the Jews,
he took them back with him

00:13:00.250 --> 00:13:05.560
as prisoners and allowed the
Jews to establish themselves

00:13:05.560 --> 00:13:09.340
in Babylon in a
relatively free manner.

00:13:09.340 --> 00:13:12.160
Why he did that, which
was very contrary

00:13:12.160 --> 00:13:21.010
to social international behavior
at the time, I don't know.

00:13:21.010 --> 00:13:26.140
What happened was
significant for the Jews.

00:13:26.140 --> 00:13:29.200
Not having a temple,
not having priests,

00:13:29.200 --> 00:13:32.140
you must understand
the organization

00:13:32.140 --> 00:13:35.480
of the social structure
around the temple.

00:13:35.480 --> 00:13:38.540
The temple was run by priests.

00:13:38.540 --> 00:13:42.610
There was no
democracy in religion.

00:13:42.610 --> 00:13:46.300
You took what the
priests gave you,

00:13:46.300 --> 00:13:53.350
and the priests were monitors
of the Holy of the Holies.

00:13:53.350 --> 00:13:57.190
If you look at the plans
putated for the first temple,

00:13:57.190 --> 00:14:01.030
you will see that structure.

00:14:01.030 --> 00:14:04.720
The Jews didn't have temples.

00:14:04.720 --> 00:14:07.000
They either had to
give up their religion

00:14:07.000 --> 00:14:12.100
or convert to some
other pagan religion.

00:14:12.100 --> 00:14:24.790
Having been the first
monoethicists of all, having--

00:14:24.790 --> 00:14:27.850
monotheism was
founded in Jerusalem.

00:14:27.850 --> 00:14:30.280
Nobody quite knows how.

00:14:30.280 --> 00:14:34.000
But the idea that many
gods were dysfunctional,

00:14:34.000 --> 00:14:38.320
and that the single God,
an invisible single God,

00:14:38.320 --> 00:14:46.230
was the proper course
for religious faith.

00:14:46.230 --> 00:14:50.870
So the Jews prayed in
houses and in schools--

00:14:50.870 --> 00:14:53.520
wherever they could.

00:14:53.520 --> 00:14:57.815
This type substitution
was an extraordinary idea.

00:15:00.410 --> 00:15:05.720
In the history of the
Church, I found a reference

00:15:05.720 --> 00:15:07.700
to saying that this
was the beginning

00:15:07.700 --> 00:15:15.710
of the idea of the
church free of the rule

00:15:15.710 --> 00:15:21.140
of plutocratic priests.

00:15:21.140 --> 00:15:24.170
People could indulge in
a critical examination

00:15:24.170 --> 00:15:29.670
of their faith
together as a group.

00:15:29.670 --> 00:15:32.390
In fact, the conflict
towards the end

00:15:32.390 --> 00:15:37.340
of the Jewish reign in
Jerusalem at the time of Jesus

00:15:37.340 --> 00:15:40.910
was very much a conflict
between the priests

00:15:40.910 --> 00:15:45.410
of the Second Temple
and the Pharisees,

00:15:45.410 --> 00:15:46.850
who were advocating--

00:15:46.850 --> 00:15:49.790
beginning to advocate
the democratic religion

00:15:49.790 --> 00:15:52.430
in the form of the synagogue.

00:15:52.430 --> 00:15:56.810
So the synagogue emerges
in primitive form

00:15:56.810 --> 00:16:00.930
in the exile of a Jewish
group from the temple.

00:16:05.930 --> 00:16:07.970
There's a second
phenomenon which

00:16:07.970 --> 00:16:10.970
occurs during this period.

00:16:10.970 --> 00:16:13.790
In the Judeo-Christian
Bible, there

00:16:13.790 --> 00:16:17.480
are seven chapters
devoted to Ezekiel.

00:16:17.480 --> 00:16:20.210
Who was Ezekiel?

00:16:20.210 --> 00:16:24.432
What role did he play in the--

00:16:24.432 --> 00:16:25.640
you should know these things.

00:16:25.640 --> 00:16:31.160
You all are
Christians, or Muslims,

00:16:31.160 --> 00:16:34.250
or any other form of religion.

00:16:34.250 --> 00:16:38.240
You know nothing about
your own religion?

00:16:38.240 --> 00:16:46.030
Maybe you're all pagans, which
would be refreshing, I suppose.

00:16:46.030 --> 00:16:48.880
AUDIENCE: He was a Catholic?

00:16:48.880 --> 00:16:54.740
JULIAN BEINART: Well,
Ezekiel had a dream.

00:16:54.740 --> 00:16:55.600
He was a prophet.

00:16:55.600 --> 00:16:59.830
He had a dream that God and
he encountered each other,

00:16:59.830 --> 00:17:05.109
and he had instructions
to devise a new temple.

00:17:05.109 --> 00:17:11.619
There are six chapters in your
Bible on Ezekiel's dimensions

00:17:11.619 --> 00:17:17.380
for this new temple.

00:17:17.380 --> 00:17:22.690
Imagine dreaming of a
temple when you're in exile

00:17:22.690 --> 00:17:27.910
and designing it in
your mind as a text.

00:17:27.910 --> 00:17:31.720
Anyway, strange things happen.

00:17:31.720 --> 00:17:36.160
Ezekiel's temple, as I'll
show you in the slides,

00:17:36.160 --> 00:17:41.510
has been redrawn and reimagined
from these dimensions

00:17:41.510 --> 00:17:42.175
over time.

00:17:44.740 --> 00:17:48.220
The Jews return, and
the third significance

00:17:48.220 --> 00:17:57.400
of the stay in Babylon,
the Jewish Talmud,

00:17:57.400 --> 00:18:01.190
the Book of Laws,
has two versions,

00:18:01.190 --> 00:18:03.010
the Palestinian version--

00:18:03.010 --> 00:18:06.820
at least the Jerusalem version
and the Babylonian version.

00:18:06.820 --> 00:18:09.160
The Babylonian
version is considered

00:18:09.160 --> 00:18:13.520
to be the preferred version.

00:18:13.520 --> 00:18:17.920
So the Jews in exile
established a culture,

00:18:17.920 --> 00:18:22.510
which they brought back to
Jerusalem having been freed,

00:18:22.510 --> 00:18:26.170
and Israel read the Bible to
the people for the first time.

00:18:26.170 --> 00:18:28.575
And according to
the text, they wept.

00:18:31.780 --> 00:18:34.450
So the beginning of
the idea that religion

00:18:34.450 --> 00:18:40.690
is a democratic phenomenon
is my explanation

00:18:40.690 --> 00:18:43.870
for the problem of Jesus.

00:18:43.870 --> 00:18:48.700
I've a rather eccentric
version of the story.

00:18:48.700 --> 00:18:54.490
What happened is
we jump 500 years,

00:18:54.490 --> 00:18:58.600
and Herod goes and
rebuilds the temple.

00:18:58.600 --> 00:19:01.255
He builds an enormous
temple-- bigger than before.

00:19:06.890 --> 00:19:09.480
The priests, again,
are in control.

00:19:12.240 --> 00:19:15.530
They control power.

00:19:15.530 --> 00:19:19.640
They control the
artifact of religion.

00:19:19.640 --> 00:19:21.230
They control property.

00:19:21.230 --> 00:19:23.315
They control
everything in the city.

00:19:26.510 --> 00:19:30.980
Along comes a Jew,
a radical Jew--

00:19:30.980 --> 00:19:33.440
has another vision of the world.

00:19:38.010 --> 00:19:42.490
Jesus doesn't threaten
the Romans very much.

00:19:42.490 --> 00:19:46.740
The Romans are used to dealing
with whatever in the empire,

00:19:46.740 --> 00:19:48.010
with infidels.

00:19:48.010 --> 00:19:52.530
They just lock them up
or cut their heads off--

00:19:52.530 --> 00:19:55.600
very explicit rules.

00:19:55.600 --> 00:20:00.570
[INAUDIBLE] in a rather
difficult situation.

00:20:00.570 --> 00:20:09.010
The priests are more threatened
by Jesus than other Romans.

00:20:09.010 --> 00:20:13.540
The priests, therefore,
connive with the Romans

00:20:13.540 --> 00:20:16.930
to execute Jesus.

00:20:16.930 --> 00:20:21.760
The notion of
execution of your son

00:20:21.760 --> 00:20:26.620
occurs in the Judeo-Christian
Bible before, and although it

00:20:26.620 --> 00:20:30.610
wasn't legal, the idea
of passing your son

00:20:30.610 --> 00:20:37.630
on as a gift, the use of blood.

00:20:37.630 --> 00:20:41.490
22,000 oxen were killed
in the dedication

00:20:41.490 --> 00:20:42.645
of the Temple of Solomon.

00:20:45.360 --> 00:20:50.610
The whole idea of giving
something to God as a gift--

00:20:50.610 --> 00:20:56.580
if you were poor, you brought
a chicken to the temple

00:20:56.580 --> 00:20:58.530
to the priest.

00:20:58.530 --> 00:21:02.550
If you were wealthy, you
brought a cow, an ox.

00:21:02.550 --> 00:21:05.010
If you were very
wealthy, good Lord knows,

00:21:05.010 --> 00:21:07.230
you donated your son.

00:21:07.230 --> 00:21:11.460
The story of Abraham and
Isaac is that same version

00:21:11.460 --> 00:21:15.630
of that gift giving.

00:21:15.630 --> 00:21:19.200
The supreme gift is
the gift of your son.

00:21:19.200 --> 00:21:23.580
And the Jesus story
is archetypally

00:21:23.580 --> 00:21:31.290
the story of God
donating his son, again,

00:21:31.290 --> 00:21:35.160
for the improvement
of the world.

00:21:35.160 --> 00:21:41.640
Christianity is based on
many mythical stories, which

00:21:41.640 --> 00:21:44.340
emanated from the
history of Jerusalem,

00:21:44.340 --> 00:21:48.025
and is the second monotheistic
religion to emerge out

00:21:48.025 --> 00:21:48.525
of the city.

00:21:57.120 --> 00:22:02.480
Muhammad is born in 570 BC.

00:22:02.480 --> 00:22:07.620
He fights his battles
in Mecca and Medina,

00:22:07.620 --> 00:22:11.970
spreads the idea of Islam as
the third great monotheistic

00:22:11.970 --> 00:22:16.530
religion through the
Arabian Peninsula,

00:22:16.530 --> 00:22:20.340
and soon afterwards,
Jerusalem is invaded

00:22:20.340 --> 00:22:23.190
by the first Arab group.

00:22:27.730 --> 00:22:31.510
Significantly, the
Christians had chosen

00:22:31.510 --> 00:22:35.890
a site for the great church.

00:22:35.890 --> 00:22:41.190
Constantine's mother,
Helena, from Istanbul

00:22:41.190 --> 00:22:45.100
or Constantinople,
drifted down to Jerusalem,

00:22:45.100 --> 00:22:47.860
and he's supposed to have
selected the site where

00:22:47.860 --> 00:22:50.500
Jesus was killed.

00:22:50.500 --> 00:22:52.450
On the basis of
that information,

00:22:52.450 --> 00:22:55.600
the Church of the Holy
Sepulcher was built

00:22:55.600 --> 00:22:59.200
and is still in existence
today, having been destroyed

00:22:59.200 --> 00:23:04.810
seven times and rebuilt.

00:23:04.810 --> 00:23:06.700
The Arabs arrive in Jerusalem.

00:23:06.700 --> 00:23:10.270
They're the newcomers.

00:23:10.270 --> 00:23:18.100
They asked the Christian
bishop about sites

00:23:18.100 --> 00:23:19.915
for their own mosque.

00:23:25.090 --> 00:23:29.710
The Temple Mount, which had been
the site of the Jewish temple,

00:23:29.710 --> 00:23:33.640
had been raised by the Romans,
and there was nothing left.

00:23:33.640 --> 00:23:36.030
For 500 years, the
Temple Mount was

00:23:36.030 --> 00:23:40.690
a rubbish dump of old parts
of buildings and so on.

00:23:40.690 --> 00:23:43.670
The Christians wanted
nothing to do with it.

00:23:43.670 --> 00:23:48.430
In fact, the Church of the Holy
Sepulcher, which was usually

00:23:48.430 --> 00:23:55.420
under the Roman city, entered
from The Cardo on the West,

00:23:55.420 --> 00:23:58.510
at least on the
East, was closed.

00:23:58.510 --> 00:24:02.350
And you now enter the
Church of the Holy Sepulcher

00:24:02.350 --> 00:24:04.510
only from the South.

00:24:04.510 --> 00:24:07.840
On the East now, there's
the best candy store

00:24:07.840 --> 00:24:09.415
in Jerusalem on The Cardo.

00:24:13.120 --> 00:24:21.130
So although the Temple
Mount, which is only two--

00:24:21.130 --> 00:24:22.870
to use their phrase--

00:24:22.870 --> 00:24:26.800
two-arrow lengths,
bow lengths, away

00:24:26.800 --> 00:24:33.670
from the Church of
the Holy Sepulcher,

00:24:33.670 --> 00:24:43.610
the Islamic penetrators thought
that the mythological origins

00:24:43.610 --> 00:24:48.380
of the use of the Temple
Mount were sufficient for them

00:24:48.380 --> 00:24:54.800
to follow the Jewish tradition
of the destroyed temple.

00:24:54.800 --> 00:24:59.570
So they rebuilt the Temple
Mount in about 100 years

00:24:59.570 --> 00:25:08.080
after Mohammad's birth and
built the two buildings

00:25:08.080 --> 00:25:09.550
which are still there today--

00:25:09.550 --> 00:25:11.670
The Dome of the Rock
and the Al-Aqsa mosque.

00:25:15.770 --> 00:25:18.680
In my writing, I go through
the detailed history

00:25:18.680 --> 00:25:24.650
of the idea of resilience,
how under these occupations

00:25:24.650 --> 00:25:28.490
each religion plays around
with the idea of permanence.

00:25:34.390 --> 00:25:39.310
The Christians in
the Holy Sepulcher

00:25:39.310 --> 00:25:43.600
never really agree
on the fundamentals

00:25:43.600 --> 00:25:45.100
of the Christian faith.

00:25:45.100 --> 00:25:47.620
Whilst they may agree
on the fundamentals,

00:25:47.620 --> 00:25:50.440
they don't agree
on its application.

00:25:50.440 --> 00:25:57.010
So 70% of the Holy Sepulcher
is still under Greek Christian.

00:25:57.010 --> 00:26:03.790
The poor African Ethiopian
Christians live on the roof

00:26:03.790 --> 00:26:08.350
and are only allowed to
enter the major tabernacle

00:26:08.350 --> 00:26:12.250
by a small staircase.

00:26:12.250 --> 00:26:18.230
As one of the writers
writes, "They're

00:26:18.230 --> 00:26:23.380
all divided by faith," or
something of this kind.

00:26:23.380 --> 00:26:31.930
So you have a notion of the
three major religions having,

00:26:31.930 --> 00:26:37.828
in the case of the
Christians, an artifact which

00:26:37.828 --> 00:26:41.980
houses divided aspects
of the religion.

00:26:41.980 --> 00:26:42.940
There are fires.

00:26:42.940 --> 00:26:44.240
They are people killed.

00:26:44.240 --> 00:26:48.340
There are all kinds
of disjunctions

00:26:48.340 --> 00:26:53.050
between these groups, but
Christianity survives.

00:26:53.050 --> 00:26:57.550
On the Islamic front,
you have the church,

00:26:57.550 --> 00:27:00.730
the Dome of the Rock, and the
Al-Aqsa mosque, which survive

00:27:00.730 --> 00:27:03.520
to this day unblemished.

00:27:03.520 --> 00:27:07.870
In 1099, the Crusaders,
under the pressure

00:27:07.870 --> 00:27:11.710
from the popes of
Europe, attempt

00:27:11.710 --> 00:27:14.100
to restore Christianity.

00:27:16.720 --> 00:27:20.980
Instead of dismant--
they are absolutely

00:27:20.980 --> 00:27:26.530
ruthless to the degree that they
kill everybody in their sight.

00:27:26.530 --> 00:27:29.620
They kill Muslims and Jews.

00:27:29.620 --> 00:27:32.560
And in the blood of
their boots, they

00:27:32.560 --> 00:27:36.320
walk to the Holy
Sepulcher and pray.

00:27:36.320 --> 00:27:42.490
There's always this kind of
interesting biblical thing,

00:27:42.490 --> 00:27:46.480
which I focus on also, that
the interpretation of God

00:27:46.480 --> 00:27:48.730
is always ambiguous.

00:27:48.730 --> 00:27:54.580
God is always punishing people
for doing the wrong things,

00:27:54.580 --> 00:27:59.050
but he's also forgiving, if
you come to terms with him--

00:27:59.050 --> 00:28:04.700
or her, depending
on what you believe.

00:28:04.700 --> 00:28:11.740
So the Crusaders behave in
this apparently bifocal way.

00:28:11.740 --> 00:28:19.060
They destroy everybody whom they
see in their sight violently,

00:28:19.060 --> 00:28:25.690
and at the same time, they go
and sing hymns in their church.

00:28:25.690 --> 00:28:31.150
There may be parallels in
contemporary violence as well.

00:28:31.150 --> 00:28:36.550
I don't know if it's a
born-in instinct in humankind,

00:28:36.550 --> 00:28:41.530
that you modify your
behavior in two distinct ways

00:28:41.530 --> 00:28:46.060
according to your belief system.

00:28:46.060 --> 00:28:49.570
The Jews have lost two temples.

00:28:49.570 --> 00:28:52.000
They now are in exile.

00:28:52.000 --> 00:28:53.560
They take with them books.

00:28:53.560 --> 00:28:56.881
That's the only
property they have.

00:28:56.881 --> 00:29:05.110
There's writers-- Herschel,
the American Jewish liberal

00:29:05.110 --> 00:29:10.390
theological rabbi, Mitchell
[INAUDIBLE] did his PhD

00:29:10.390 --> 00:29:11.590
at MIT--

00:29:11.590 --> 00:29:15.970
write about the idea
of the Jewish book

00:29:15.970 --> 00:29:21.580
as the significant
property of memory.

00:29:21.580 --> 00:29:23.800
They argue that,
in fact, they are--

00:29:23.800 --> 00:29:27.580
I think it's Herschel that
talks about the Jewish religion

00:29:27.580 --> 00:29:32.540
as being a religion of
the architecture of time.

00:29:32.540 --> 00:29:38.140
If you look at the layout
of a text in the Mishnah,

00:29:38.140 --> 00:29:41.800
you'll see a body of writing.

00:29:41.800 --> 00:29:47.230
And on the sides are
Talmudic interpretations

00:29:47.230 --> 00:29:50.540
by rabbis over time.

00:29:50.540 --> 00:29:56.260
So the truth is never
absolute in this one sense--

00:29:56.260 --> 00:30:01.190
that it's always
open to discussion.

00:30:01.190 --> 00:30:04.240
It's also that the Jews
took upon themselves--

00:30:04.240 --> 00:30:09.280
and Freud himself, who at
one time thought about going

00:30:09.280 --> 00:30:10.510
to live in Jerusalem--

00:30:13.150 --> 00:30:17.620
says that the Jews
preoccupied themselves

00:30:17.620 --> 00:30:20.770
with avoiding pictorial imagery.

00:30:20.770 --> 00:30:24.580
You cannot decorate
the synagogue.

00:30:24.580 --> 00:30:29.080
The text has to be
absolutely pure.

00:30:29.080 --> 00:30:31.340
Jews didn't become architects.

00:30:31.340 --> 00:30:34.390
They were never in a
power position in exile

00:30:34.390 --> 00:30:36.160
for thousands of years--

00:30:36.160 --> 00:30:37.990
well, not thousands of years.

00:30:37.990 --> 00:30:40.660
Peter Eisenman and his--

00:30:40.660 --> 00:30:42.190
Frank Gehry are Jewish.

00:30:42.190 --> 00:30:46.540
And I suppose that we've
made up for that lost time.

00:30:49.660 --> 00:30:55.510
But the Jewish
presence after 70 AD

00:30:55.510 --> 00:31:01.690
was in exile until the
slow return of the Jews

00:31:01.690 --> 00:31:12.570
in the Ottoman period, which
lasted from about 1500 to 1917.

00:31:12.570 --> 00:31:16.350
I hope you're following all
of these detailed stories.

00:31:16.350 --> 00:31:21.360
But in a sense,
it's only by looking

00:31:21.360 --> 00:31:24.840
at the detailed
side of the stories

00:31:24.840 --> 00:31:28.260
that you really get a good
idea of the complexity

00:31:28.260 --> 00:31:30.060
of the situation.

00:31:30.060 --> 00:31:31.920
To say Arab--

00:31:31.920 --> 00:31:36.210
I mean, of the 3,000 years
of the history of Jerusalem,

00:31:36.210 --> 00:31:39.870
1,200 years would be under
the Israelites or the Jews,

00:31:39.870 --> 00:31:42.510
and 1,200 years under
the Arabs or Islam.

00:31:45.820 --> 00:31:50.685
Whatever that means, the rest is
divided amongst the Christians

00:31:50.685 --> 00:31:51.310
and the Romans.

00:31:54.000 --> 00:31:55.990
Jerusalem was, in
the first place,

00:31:55.990 --> 00:31:59.840
not a particularly
important city.

00:31:59.840 --> 00:32:00.910
It was too steep.

00:32:03.980 --> 00:32:10.130
The main circulation
path was to the West

00:32:10.130 --> 00:32:13.340
along the Mediterranean.

00:32:13.340 --> 00:32:20.210
Jerusalem was the last connector
between the coastal plain

00:32:20.210 --> 00:32:24.375
and the endless desert, which
stretched all the way to India.

00:32:27.630 --> 00:32:32.850
The Dead Sea close to Jerusalem
was the lowest point on Earth.

00:32:32.850 --> 00:32:35.790
So there was-- I'll show
you a slide indicating

00:32:35.790 --> 00:32:39.390
this division, geographical
division, on which Jerusalem

00:32:39.390 --> 00:32:41.160
sits.

00:32:41.160 --> 00:32:45.210
Alexander the Great
visited Jerusalem.

00:32:45.210 --> 00:32:49.650
This was an enormous
victory for the Jews.

00:32:49.650 --> 00:32:56.160
Many Jews, including my
son, are named Alexander

00:32:56.160 --> 00:32:58.890
because of that tradition.

00:32:58.890 --> 00:33:03.690
His first name is Peter, but
his second name is Alexander.

00:33:03.690 --> 00:33:10.380
I named him after the
Russian giants rather

00:33:10.380 --> 00:33:12.555
and Jewish heroes.

00:33:15.790 --> 00:33:26.810
So Zionism, as a
phenomenon, occurs in Europe

00:33:26.810 --> 00:33:32.420
as a consequence of the
marginalization of Jews

00:33:32.420 --> 00:33:39.360
in Central Europe and all the
way to England and France,

00:33:39.360 --> 00:33:41.982
the disposition of Jewish land.

00:33:41.982 --> 00:33:45.990
The Jews, under
one of the early I

00:33:45.990 --> 00:33:49.830
think 12th century English
kings, had to wear labels

00:33:49.830 --> 00:33:52.830
marking them as Jews--

00:33:52.830 --> 00:33:55.410
the pogroms of Eastern Europe.

00:33:55.410 --> 00:34:03.000
I mean, it's a long history
which precedes the Holocaust.

00:34:03.000 --> 00:34:09.090
And Jewish reaction to
persecution and punishment

00:34:09.090 --> 00:34:13.320
took the form of a biblical
notion of "next year

00:34:13.320 --> 00:34:15.090
in Jerusalem."

00:34:15.090 --> 00:34:17.519
In the Jewish Passover
service, there

00:34:17.519 --> 00:34:21.510
is this phrase, "next
year, in Jerusalem."

00:34:21.510 --> 00:34:25.320
The Jewish Passover, unlike
the Christian Easter,

00:34:25.320 --> 00:34:30.120
is not dedicated very
much to a religious idea,

00:34:30.120 --> 00:34:38.920
but related to the escape
under Moses from Egypt and God

00:34:38.920 --> 00:34:44.270
parting the Red Sea to
allow the Jews to escape.

00:34:44.270 --> 00:34:50.060
How true that story is, whether
Freud claims that Moses was,

00:34:50.060 --> 00:34:56.375
in fact, an Egyptian who
had learned about it.

00:34:56.375 --> 00:35:01.400
Well, anyway, there
are too many stories.

00:35:01.400 --> 00:35:04.130
When you get all of
these people having

00:35:04.130 --> 00:35:09.810
been involved in this
dialogue, on this multilogue,

00:35:09.810 --> 00:35:12.750
you have many stories.

00:35:12.750 --> 00:35:18.600
The Ottoman Empire chooses to
take the wrong side in the 1418

00:35:18.600 --> 00:35:21.840
war, and the British
take over Jerusalem.

00:35:21.840 --> 00:35:24.210
They maintain
Jerusalem as a mandate

00:35:24.210 --> 00:35:31.290
until 1948, when the
War of Independence

00:35:31.290 --> 00:35:36.660
and the Jewish state of Israel
was founded 70 years ago now.

00:35:41.800 --> 00:35:46.120
East Jerusalem belongs to
Jordan, West Jerusalem,

00:35:46.120 --> 00:35:49.470
to Israel.

00:35:49.470 --> 00:35:53.220
1967, there's another war.

00:35:53.220 --> 00:36:00.880
This time, the Jews expel
Jordan from East Jerusalem,

00:36:00.880 --> 00:36:05.605
and in fact, annex the West
Bank to a united Israel.

00:36:08.150 --> 00:36:12.850
The United Nations
proposes that Jerusalem

00:36:12.850 --> 00:36:17.020
be an international city.

00:36:17.020 --> 00:36:21.190
They actually have a diagram
of the form of Jerusalem

00:36:21.190 --> 00:36:23.500
as an international city.

00:36:23.500 --> 00:36:30.370
Neither side, neither
Arab nor Jewish politics,

00:36:30.370 --> 00:36:32.560
accept that as a resolution.

00:36:35.380 --> 00:36:41.680
The Jews start, after the
Oslo Accords, which presumably

00:36:41.680 --> 00:36:46.540
sets out that there would be an
independent Palestinian state,

00:36:46.540 --> 00:36:51.850
and talks about the
'67 boundary lines

00:36:51.850 --> 00:36:55.780
and zones for the future states.

00:36:59.620 --> 00:37:04.870
Israel politics, a combination
of religious pressure

00:37:04.870 --> 00:37:15.010
and all kinds of other
internal Israeli social issues,

00:37:15.010 --> 00:37:18.070
promote the expansion
program, which

00:37:18.070 --> 00:37:21.910
now has reached
300,000 settlers living

00:37:21.910 --> 00:37:30.810
on land, which is East of the
partition line set by the Oslo

00:37:30.810 --> 00:37:31.310
Accords.

00:37:36.910 --> 00:37:41.800
Many American presidents,
since Harry Truman I think,

00:37:41.800 --> 00:37:46.300
have objected to Israeli
settlement expansion,

00:37:46.300 --> 00:37:48.250
with no results whatsoever.

00:37:50.800 --> 00:37:55.630
The status quo, at the end of
all of my long story of 3,000

00:37:55.630 --> 00:38:01.240
years, is a situation
in which Jerusalem

00:38:01.240 --> 00:38:06.290
is claimed by Israel to be
the unique capital of Israel.

00:38:06.290 --> 00:38:09.130
Although, as you will
read in my letter,

00:38:09.130 --> 00:38:14.320
many of the previous
Israeli presidents

00:38:14.320 --> 00:38:17.380
have looked for
alternative sites

00:38:17.380 --> 00:38:24.460
to Jerusalem, at least for the
capital of Israel, including

00:38:24.460 --> 00:38:27.845
Ben-Gurion's choice of
coordinate in the Negev.

00:38:34.030 --> 00:38:40.180
At present, the
Palestinian position

00:38:40.180 --> 00:38:42.580
is a slightly more
complex position,

00:38:42.580 --> 00:38:46.450
but they would like
to share Jerusalem

00:38:46.450 --> 00:38:50.450
as the capital of
their state as well.

00:38:50.450 --> 00:38:55.090
So you have a notion, which
I don't think exists anywhere

00:38:55.090 --> 00:38:56.980
else in the world,
where one city is

00:38:56.980 --> 00:39:00.800
the capital of two countries.

00:39:00.800 --> 00:39:06.230
You get St. Louis, Missouri
and St. Louis, Kansas City.

00:39:06.230 --> 00:39:11.690
You have divisions in
other parts of the world,

00:39:11.690 --> 00:39:15.080
but you have no claim
for a city as being

00:39:15.080 --> 00:39:18.180
the capital of two states.

00:39:18.180 --> 00:39:24.680
In fact, the notion of two
states is now under discussion.

00:39:24.680 --> 00:39:27.380
There's a new,
relatively new, movement,

00:39:27.380 --> 00:39:32.150
which argues for the existence
of a single state, which

00:39:32.150 --> 00:39:35.240
would alleviate the
problem of the settlements,

00:39:35.240 --> 00:39:38.450
but deny Zionist ambitions.

00:39:38.450 --> 00:39:44.260
Because demographically,
the Jewish position

00:39:44.260 --> 00:39:49.330
is more vulnerable
demographically.

00:39:49.330 --> 00:39:52.990
This two-state solution,
which the United States

00:39:52.990 --> 00:39:59.710
and most liberal
politicians support,

00:39:59.710 --> 00:40:03.175
is for there to be an
independent Palestinian state.

00:40:05.770 --> 00:40:10.990
The Palestinians wish to go
back to the 1967 boundary.

00:40:10.990 --> 00:40:13.150
They'll have to be
some compromise.

00:40:13.150 --> 00:40:15.280
God knows how that
compromise is going

00:40:15.280 --> 00:40:19.540
to be worked out between
the size of the settlement

00:40:19.540 --> 00:40:25.750
population and the
emaciated, fragmented--

00:40:25.750 --> 00:40:30.430
you can see in the last
map in your handout,

00:40:30.430 --> 00:40:34.760
just in the case of the
periphery of Jerusalem,

00:40:34.760 --> 00:40:47.960
how much this land has become
parcelized and fragmented

00:40:47.960 --> 00:40:48.905
rather than unified.

00:40:54.370 --> 00:41:01.850
My son's book, which tackles
this problem much more

00:41:01.850 --> 00:41:11.270
eloquently than I can, argues
that for a Palestinian state,

00:41:11.270 --> 00:41:16.150
which is liberal and not
imposing military law

00:41:16.150 --> 00:41:19.880
onto the Palestinians
in the West Bank,

00:41:19.880 --> 00:41:23.060
and so on, and so
on, is probably

00:41:23.060 --> 00:41:26.420
the most coherent
liberal position

00:41:26.420 --> 00:41:28.700
on the subject at the moment.

00:41:28.700 --> 00:41:33.500
The future of Jerusalem
may well be never resolved.

00:41:38.460 --> 00:41:44.940
It may be the result of too much
history and too much mythology.

00:41:44.940 --> 00:41:49.050
Mythology becomes history
at a certain point.

00:41:49.050 --> 00:41:51.360
Let me give you an example.

00:41:51.360 --> 00:41:57.450
Christians, at Easter today,
celebrate the way of the cross.

00:41:57.450 --> 00:42:00.330
They carry the
cross symbolically

00:42:00.330 --> 00:42:04.500
from the praetorium
where Jesus was housed

00:42:04.500 --> 00:42:09.370
to where he was crucified.

00:42:09.370 --> 00:42:13.510
The site of the crucifixion
is not absolutely clear,

00:42:13.510 --> 00:42:18.790
but most people now assume it
to be somewhere around where

00:42:18.790 --> 00:42:22.300
the sepulcher is.

00:42:22.300 --> 00:42:27.610
One of the stations of
the cross, station number

00:42:27.610 --> 00:42:29.710
I don't know what--

00:42:29.710 --> 00:42:32.710
number seven, I'm
not sure exactly--

00:42:32.710 --> 00:42:36.460
it's called the
Ecce Homo station.

00:42:36.460 --> 00:42:46.065
That's where the Roman Legion
commander pointed down to Jesus

00:42:46.065 --> 00:42:47.510
and said, ecce homo--

00:42:47.510 --> 00:42:52.400
look at that man, look at this
man in a derisive manner--

00:42:52.400 --> 00:42:55.770
carrying the cross.

00:42:55.770 --> 00:42:59.340
In fact, history proves that
to be absolutely nonsense,

00:42:59.340 --> 00:43:01.740
but a complete myth.

00:43:01.740 --> 00:43:07.800
Archeologists say that the Ecce
Homo Arch was only built long

00:43:07.800 --> 00:43:15.160
after Jesus' death and didn't
exist at the time of Jesus.

00:43:15.160 --> 00:43:24.210
So the other
conflations of reality,

00:43:24.210 --> 00:43:30.690
