endured the Nusaybah family,

01:04:40.380 --> 01:04:45.540
an Israeli Islamic
family, with the keys.

01:04:48.340 --> 01:04:51.155
Here is the entrance
to the south.

01:04:51.155 --> 01:04:51.655
Next.

01:04:54.480 --> 01:04:55.275
Here's the roof.

01:04:57.920 --> 01:05:02.120
A Christian priest living
on the roof of the Church

01:05:02.120 --> 01:05:05.330
of the Holy Sepulcher
in semi-exile, and here

01:05:05.330 --> 01:05:10.455
is an Easter night
celebration on the roof.

01:05:10.455 --> 01:05:10.955
Next.

01:05:14.870 --> 01:05:18.450
The establishment,
first establishment,

01:05:18.450 --> 01:05:22.740
of the Dome of the Rock, the
circular purple building,

01:05:22.740 --> 01:05:26.760
and the Al-Aqsa
mosque on the south,

01:05:26.760 --> 01:05:35.340
and the many
institutions leaving

01:05:35.340 --> 01:05:41.745
this part of the holy city
to be the Jewish quarter.

01:05:44.920 --> 01:05:47.590
The Basilica of Holy Zion--

01:05:47.590 --> 01:05:51.220
slowly there's something
about the Armenian quarter

01:05:51.220 --> 01:05:56.165
and the Christian quarter to
develop further to the north.

01:05:56.165 --> 01:05:56.665
Next.

01:06:01.860 --> 01:06:06.540
The Dome of the Rock,
that Al-Aqsa mosque--

01:06:06.540 --> 01:06:07.040
next.

01:06:11.920 --> 01:06:17.230
The Crusader period for
a relatively short time,

01:06:17.230 --> 01:06:22.700
the [LATIN],, the baptistery,
the Temple Salomonis,

01:06:22.700 --> 01:06:28.300
the previous Al-Aqsa mosque,
not destroyed but maintained,

01:06:28.300 --> 01:06:32.830
only Christianized
in a simple way--

01:06:32.830 --> 01:06:35.080
all the Christian
institutions which

01:06:35.080 --> 01:06:37.900
grow up under the Crusader.

01:06:37.900 --> 01:06:42.820
St. James Cathedral, the Greek
hopice, the Syrian monastery,

01:06:42.820 --> 01:06:46.360
the church of St. Martin,
St. John the Baptist,

01:06:46.360 --> 01:06:49.210
the Hospitaliers
quarter, the building

01:06:49.210 --> 01:06:55.940
of the largest
hospital in the world

01:06:55.940 --> 01:07:01.450
at that time in the
Muristan district,

01:07:01.450 --> 01:07:08.030
largely part of the
Christianic beneficence.

01:07:08.030 --> 01:07:08.530
Next.

01:07:13.080 --> 01:07:29.010
The retaking of the city under
Arab Islamic circumstances

01:07:29.010 --> 01:07:33.150
by Saladin, rebuilding
of the walls,

01:07:33.150 --> 01:07:40.920
the wall's rebuilt in 1131,
1191 to 1213, all of the schools

01:07:40.920 --> 01:07:45.840
and community places as a
result of the Islamicization

01:07:45.840 --> 01:07:48.360
of this space.

01:07:48.360 --> 01:07:54.820
1917, Jerusalem prior, at the
time of the British invasion.

01:07:54.820 --> 01:07:55.320
Next.

01:08:01.640 --> 01:08:05.240
I mentioned the example
of the [INAUDIBLE],,

01:08:05.240 --> 01:08:13.130
the layering of David's
tomb, the Dormitian Abbey,

01:08:13.130 --> 01:08:17.779
and the [INAUDIBLE]
Caiaphas, one of the agents

01:08:17.779 --> 01:08:20.689
in the death of Jesus.

01:08:20.689 --> 01:08:25.430
But the Last Supper takes
place there as well.

01:08:25.430 --> 01:08:28.310
Here is the Dormitian
Abbey, which

01:08:28.310 --> 01:08:33.500
has these three layers of
vertical space belonging

01:08:33.500 --> 01:08:34.830
to different religions.

01:08:34.830 --> 01:08:35.330
Next.

01:08:43.420 --> 01:08:48.729
The final subdivision of the
Holy City into four sectors,

01:08:48.729 --> 01:08:53.560
the Dome of the Rock,
and the Al-Aqsa mosque,

01:08:53.560 --> 01:08:57.279
penetrating into the Jewish
sector with the Dung Gate.

01:08:57.279 --> 01:08:59.140
That's this gate.

01:08:59.140 --> 01:09:03.490
The Golden Gate, which
is not open any longer

01:09:03.490 --> 01:09:05.950
to the Islamic
section, which has

01:09:05.950 --> 01:09:12.160
the Damascus Gate on the
north as its major entrance.

01:09:12.160 --> 01:09:13.840
The Church of the
Holy Sepulcher,

01:09:13.840 --> 01:09:17.590
and the Christian sector,
and the Armenian sector here.

01:09:17.590 --> 01:09:19.720
The Jaffa Gate leads to--

01:09:19.720 --> 01:09:22.540
is the prime-- if you
extend these lines,

01:09:22.540 --> 01:09:28.210
the Jaffa Gate extends
to the Mediterranean.

01:09:28.210 --> 01:09:31.000
The Dung Gate extends
down to Egypt.

01:09:31.000 --> 01:09:35.109
The Damascus Gate
extends upwards to Syria,

01:09:35.109 --> 01:09:42.970
and this closed Golden Gate
potentially extends eastwards

01:09:42.970 --> 01:09:44.750
to Iraq.

01:09:44.750 --> 01:09:45.250
Next.

01:09:52.310 --> 01:09:55.400
The contemporary
city on the left,

01:09:55.400 --> 01:10:00.800
the coexistence of
tall skyscrapers

01:10:00.800 --> 01:10:03.695
on the west in the Jewish city.

01:10:06.425 --> 01:10:06.925
Next.

01:10:11.890 --> 01:10:15.420
The British occupation,
the McLean Plan,

01:10:15.420 --> 01:10:20.740
it's not very clear,
but it's an attempt

01:10:20.740 --> 01:10:27.040
to recognize the western part,
the Jewish part, and developing

01:10:27.040 --> 01:10:31.060
it according to a
garden city model.

01:10:31.060 --> 01:10:37.680
The Arab side is left gray for
reasons I don't understand.

01:10:37.680 --> 01:10:41.680
Restricted building
and open space--

01:10:41.680 --> 01:10:42.865
extraordinary plan.

01:10:46.280 --> 01:10:52.580
And the United Nations' plan,
which encloses a larger area

01:10:52.580 --> 01:11:02.940
than the municipality, and it
encloses Bethlehem [INAUDIBLE]

01:11:02.940 --> 01:11:06.510
on the east, including Hadassah
Hospital and Hebrew University

01:11:06.510 --> 01:11:07.752
on the northeast--

01:11:11.490 --> 01:11:13.120
rejected by both sides.

01:11:17.620 --> 01:11:18.120
Next.

01:11:23.660 --> 01:11:26.510
Jerusalem's rulers from 587--

01:11:26.510 --> 01:11:33.110
that's Nebuchadnezzar
and Babylon to 1967 AD--

01:11:33.110 --> 01:11:41.030
showing that Jerusalem had
consequence at a distance.

01:11:41.030 --> 01:11:48.890
The 1967 dividing of the
city in the east and west

01:11:48.890 --> 01:11:51.395
with a boundary between the two.

01:11:51.395 --> 01:11:51.895
Next.

01:11:54.440 --> 01:11:58.280
The boundary taken over
and a map showing--

01:12:02.100 --> 01:12:09.110
map by protagonists
of the Arab cause,

01:12:09.110 --> 01:12:11.660
arguing that the
Jews have always

01:12:11.660 --> 01:12:19.130
tried to locate settlements in
a pattern which causes the city

01:12:19.130 --> 01:12:21.060
not to be unified.

01:12:21.060 --> 01:12:21.560
Next.

01:12:27.550 --> 01:12:30.730
Louis Kahn's-- one of the
Louis Kahn's great buildings,

01:12:30.730 --> 01:12:40.590
which he never built, and his
very interesting interpretation

01:12:40.590 --> 01:12:45.740
of the use of ruins
in a city of--

01:12:45.740 --> 01:12:48.070
could you just turn on
those lights, please?

01:12:59.960 --> 01:13:08.770
When you have the intersection
of religion, politics,

01:13:08.770 --> 01:13:13.480
geography, and history,
you cannot do anything.

01:13:16.840 --> 01:13:19.600
It's frozen.

01:13:19.600 --> 01:13:23.620
I don't know of a situation
which has managed to overcome--

01:13:23.620 --> 01:13:24.925
maybe Belgian.

01:13:29.410 --> 01:13:37.540
I suppose in Europe at
least the elimination

01:13:37.540 --> 01:13:42.010
of obstacles towards
the creation of a plane

01:13:42.010 --> 01:13:44.710
of general acceptance.

01:13:44.710 --> 01:13:46.930
And the European
Union is perhaps

01:13:46.930 --> 01:13:54.100
the most modern example of
the breaking down of barriers.

01:13:54.100 --> 01:14:01.510
The barriers are still
between Algiers and Paris.

01:14:01.510 --> 01:14:06.100
It's between the hinterland
of countries, Turkey

01:14:06.100 --> 01:14:12.470
and the European Union, sending
migrant labor back and forth.

01:14:12.470 --> 01:14:19.330
But this is a
phenomenon which is not

01:14:19.330 --> 01:14:22.870
easily applied to Jerusalem.

01:14:22.870 --> 01:14:24.865
In the case of
Johannesburg, you will

01:14:24.865 --> 01:14:27.040
see the absence of religion.

01:14:27.040 --> 01:14:31.030
It is purely a question of race.

01:14:31.030 --> 01:14:35.890
Once you eliminate region
and you only deal with race,

01:14:35.890 --> 01:14:40.220
you find it easier to resolve,
even although South Africa

01:14:40.220 --> 01:14:46.330
has struggled into the
post-apartheid democracy.

01:14:46.330 --> 01:14:50.740
It took enormous resources,
and time, and bloodshed.

01:14:50.740 --> 01:15:03.960
And Johannesburg is an
artifact of race, and so on.

01:15:03.960 --> 01:15:06.900
So we look at these others
in a slightly different light

01:15:06.900 --> 01:15:08.310
than Jerusalem.

01:15:08.310 --> 01:15:14.130
But Jerusalem is the great
metaphysical city of the world.

01:15:14.130 --> 01:15:17.010
It's the most important
metaphysical presence.

01:15:24.530 --> 01:15:31.190
What that means, meaning-wise,
is difficult to say.

01:15:31.190 --> 01:15:35.270
They are parts where you tread
and walk softly and slowly,

01:15:35.270 --> 01:15:38.810
because you have a
history of associations

01:15:38.810 --> 01:15:42.000
with that particular place.

01:15:42.000 --> 01:15:44.090
And these associations
are carefully vivid.

01:15:47.620 --> 01:15:52.940
There have been
Palestinian riots

01:15:52.940 --> 01:15:58.320
around the archaeology
of certain regions

01:15:58.320 --> 01:15:59.205
in the olden city.

01:16:03.320 --> 01:16:08.090
Somebody one day will try to
excavate under the Holy Mount

01:16:08.090 --> 01:16:12.590
to see if the Holies
of Holy is still there.

01:16:12.590 --> 01:16:18.800
Steven Spielberg's probably
likely to do the movie.

01:16:18.800 --> 01:16:24.860
Although, he's done a
movie which is similar.

01:16:24.860 --> 01:16:28.100
Anyway, any thoughts
about all of this?

01:16:34.060 --> 01:16:36.240
Complexity is an easy evasion.

01:16:38.950 --> 01:16:43.060
You know, wherever I go around
the world hearing people talk

01:16:43.060 --> 01:16:45.310
about cities, the
modern interpretation

01:16:45.310 --> 01:16:49.930
is they're too complex to
have theories about them.

01:16:49.930 --> 01:16:54.700
And no city is more
complex than Jerusalem.

01:16:54.700 --> 01:17:00.250
No city has been the site
of three major religions.

01:17:00.250 --> 01:17:09.420
No city has been the site
of 3,000 years of invasion

01:17:09.420 --> 01:17:15.710
and succession, resilience
and the building

01:17:15.710 --> 01:17:17.120
up of history and myths.

01:17:22.320 --> 01:17:24.870
You should go and visit it.

01:17:24.870 --> 01:17:27.330
That's all I can recommend.

01:17:27.330 --> 01:17:31.170
See if you can make
any sense of it.

01:17:31.170 --> 01:17:33.210
You've lived in
Jerusalem, haven't you?

01:17:33.210 --> 01:17:34.920
AUDIENCE: I never
lived in Jerusalem.

01:17:34.920 --> 01:17:36.327
JULIAN BEINART: You never--

01:17:36.327 --> 01:17:38.160
AUDIENCE: I've been
there hundreds of times,

01:17:38.160 --> 01:17:40.915
but never [INAUDIBLE]
for more than one night.

01:17:40.915 --> 01:17:41.790
JULIAN BEINART: Yeah.

01:17:47.630 --> 01:17:51.980
The first immigrant
Zionists saw Jerusalem

01:17:51.980 --> 01:17:56.870
as an old-fashioned
historically-bound city.

01:17:56.870 --> 01:18:06.710
And [INAUDIBLE] chose to
make Tel Aviv the capital,

01:18:06.710 --> 01:18:10.820
or Haifa the capital
facing the Mediterranean,

01:18:10.820 --> 01:18:19.390
or in the case of Ben-Gurion,
the new city of [INAUDIBLE]..

01:18:19.390 --> 01:18:23.540
It's Chaim Weizmann
who found Jerusalem

01:18:23.540 --> 01:18:30.320
to be archaic and medieval, and
the new Jewish Zionist spirit

01:18:30.320 --> 01:18:41.590
was in favor of novelty
and social equity, and some

01:18:41.590 --> 01:18:46.420
of the things which it hasn't
been able to perpetuate.

01:18:46.420 --> 01:18:49.450
OK, we'll do
Johannesburg on Thursday

01:18:49.450 --> 01:18:52.590
and see if there's
any comparison.